channel.title: C'ya Around Mopar
channel.description:
C'ya All Around. I've decided to leave Moparisthebest. Leave Mopar all together.I was just starting to learn SCAR too. But, hey, that's life. I have no idea why I am quitting, but I'm sick of it. I wish you all the very best. And I know I made some "Net-Friendships" that will stay in my mind all my life. "Blah Blah You'll be back" Posts are just retarded. We'll see who's back. I might every now and a then pop on and make the odd reply ;) Well, I'll leave my opinion on a lot of people;
Pookey71: Honestly, one of the most nicest people you'll ever meet on the internet. Eh, shows what a couple of 12 year olds can do. I remember when I first came to this site. I Private messages him asking how to make a server... And you know what? He private messaged me back saying "Add my MSN -email here-" And I'll guide you. And he did exactly that. Helped me make my first RuneScape Server.
Alexia: Even though we didn't see eye-to-eye to on alot of things. I always found you a very VERY loyal person. You have skills in Paint and Photoshop. Don't throw them away. From what I gathered before when I was a user on Moparscape.org, I saw you make your first tutorial. Now I pop over there to see what's happening, and you're making AWESOME tutorials. I wish you the best luck in X-Cel too. Sorry I was never an active user.
Pwnd: Even though you were a jack-ass to me at times. Mind you, very rarely, but there were sometimes. I reckon you're an awesome moderator.
Frank_: Well, what can I say? Alot of you people have a very bad opinion of him. But, I've known him since I have been on Mopar, and he's always helped me. On MSN.... Even through Mopar's PM service. I hope you all learn that frank is actually a good person. He has slipped up here and there, but just live through it.
Mr.Chris: Please, someone put words in my mouth. Your artwork on the computer is tremendous. I wonder if you're that good in real life. You have some skills buddy.
k0rupt.Net: Buddy, we were never friends... Nor did we ever really speak, but christ, you are one hell of a worker. I think you filled everyone of my requests for programs. Thanks a lot Korupt.
Moparisthebest: Well, let me start by saying thank you for making such an awesome Website. And thank you for all the nice discussions we had in mIRC about bikes car's and engines. It was great being able to get into finer detail with bikes and car's and engines with you. Thank you Mopar.
Wonderguy6: Wow, me and you got on like a house on fire (He'll know what I mean, it's an Australian phrase). I don't know why, but I always seemed to be able to talk to you easily.
BloodRayne: There's nothing that I can put into words to describe you. But, you're an awesome person. Sorry if you feel shafted because of the short text describing you, but there's no way I can put it into words.
System79: Man, we had some good times on Mopar eh? We'll, we can still continue on MSN. You're one of the nicest guys on this server, and one of the best Coders. In Java, you're honestly amazing.
PaulT: Man! You're so funny. I loved reading your posts and still do! They're hilarious!
AfterMath: Hey man, we were never really friends, but your one of the most descent person on this forum! Easily. We never really spoke, talked and stuff, but you were a descent guy. I wish you the best luck in life.
Mopman: Hey man, part of the YZ faith aye? Yeah, loved talking to you on mIRC about YZ's and bikes and CBR's and stuff. Good luck in life mate.
Fast Ballz: Hey mate, you got some serious skills in Photoshop. Keep at it, thanks for all the help on Mopar. I'll talk to you on MSN :P
I'm Sorry if I missed anyone out. They're just the people that come instantly to thought. C'ya all Mopar. I wouldn't count me fully off the site, the odd post here and there ;) I wish every single one of you the best luck in life, and to stay safe, and lead a great life. Even the people that are gay Fagget Michael Jackson wanna-be's. It's probably just me you didn't get along with :P.
Later Mopar! Yz85Racer~
My last 4 words! Yz85BW's For The Win!
